      Description:
      UGREEN RJ45 crimp connectors plugs, which is made of durable oxygen-free copper and plastic materials, and suitable for Cat5e and Cat5 cable. It is perfect for building custom length network cables, and convenient for personal use and easily connected

      Kasey
      4.0 out of 5 stars Working okay for solid core UTP
      Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2017
      Verified Purchase
      These are a bit confusing but work fine. The product information says they are for solid or stranded core, however the picture shows a contact designed for stranded core, the box they come in only says stranded core, but the tri-point contact design in the plugs received appears to be for stranded and solid core (matching the product description). Regardless of all that I used them on a solid core CAT-5e and they seem to be working fine for now. I don't have the equipment to test the quality of the connection.

      NickR
      3.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, but slightly undersized
      Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2018
      Verified Purchase
      I've used these connectors to terminate a couple cat 5e (solid) cables, and have found them to be clear - fairly easy to ensure the strands are in the correct/same order on both ends, sturdy, and easy to crimp. However like one other reviewer/commentator I found them to be just a little short from the end of the locking tab to the very front of the connector. This means that the plug can be inserted securely (the tab to prevent removal is engaged) but the plug can still wiggle enough that the connectors lose contact. This is not such a problem with cables for personal use where I can be careful to ensure they're always completely seated, but using these for customer or client installs I imagine would lead to problems.
